# the machine hyper summons when the operator speaks: one command, one
# visible setting. {prompt} stands for the summon instruction; brief.md
# is written fresh beside this file at every summon, for any harness to
# read. anything that takes a prompt slots in — claude today, codex or
# another harness tomorrow. HYPER_MACHINE in the environment overrides
# this file (testing).
claude -p {prompt} --permission-mode acceptEdits
